message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Ukraine in the past 100 years is the Ukrainian Revolution of 1917-1921, which included the Ukrainian War of Independence. This revolution occurred during the chaos of World War I and the collapse of the Russian Empire. It led to the establishment of the Ukrainian People's Republic and a period of intense political and military struggle for Ukrainian independence. The revolution had a lasting impact on the country and shaped its political history in subsequent years.
